                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Lima, July 8: Reliance Industries (RIL) has signed an agreement with Perus Perupetro to jointly explore oil and gas in the Andean country, the president of Perus state-run firm said. Well be formalising the agreements reached these past weeks, and we will provide details of the joint exploration venture in areas that hold oil and gas potential, Cesar Gutierrez told Perus official news agency.                            
	 New York, July 8: Crude oil for August delivery fell $3.56 to $137.81 a barrel on the New York mercantile exchange as signs of global economic slowdown prompted investors to sell commodities.                             
	 New Delhi, July 8: The countrys tea exports have increased by nearly two per cent to 10.83 million kg in May this year compared with 9.29 million kg in the same month last year.                             
	 New York, July 8: Orient-Express, which had spurned an alliance offer from its largest non-promoter shareholder Tata Group, intends to establish a strategic partnership with a real estate developer in the US.                            
	 Manila, July 8: Many developing countries are paying higher salaries to their state employees and stunting economic growth in the process, a study by the Asian Development Bank (ADB) shows.                                                                                                                         
